text: Pyhäjoki is a municipality in Northern Ostrobothnia, Finland. As of 31 December 2023, 2,980 people lived there. Neighbouring municipalities are Kalajoki, Merijärvi, Oulainen and Raahe. It was founded in 1865. == Other websites == * Municipality of Pyhäjoki – Official website Category:Municipalities of North Ostrobothnia Category:1865 establishments in Finland
